<subSubSection id="C328ABCEFFB748067BB0FB30FAD44903" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8DF845FFB748067BB0FB30FEE74BE2" blockId="10.[189,324,1248,1274]" box="[189,324,1248,1274]" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">
<heading id="D0C54F29FFB748067BB0FB30FEE74BE2" bold="true" box="[189,324,1248,1274]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB748067BB0FB30FEE74BE2" bold="true" box="[189,324,1248,1274]" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DF845FFB748067BB0FADFFB1B4AAE" blockId="10.[187,1399,1295,1462]" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">
<bibRefCitation id="EFA385B4FFB748067BB0FADFFECB4A31" author="Kieffer J. J." box="[189,360,1295,1321]" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" pagination="57 - 96" refId="ref20278" refString="Kieffer J. J. 1909. Description of new zoophagous cynipids. Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire naturelle de Metz 26: 57 - 96. [In French.]" type="journal article" year="1909">Kieffer (1909)</bibRefCitation>
described an American species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFB74806781CFADFFC294A31" authorityName="Dalman" authorityYear="1823" box="[785,906,1295,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Anacharis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB74806781CFADFFC294A31" box="[785,906,1295,1321]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">Anacharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFB7480678BEFADFFBF24A31" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1909" box="[947,1105,1295,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Anacharis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB7480678BEFADFFBF24A31" box="[947,1105,1295,1321]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">A. flavicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. One year after, another species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFB748067A39FAE2FE0E4A54" authorityName="Dalman" authorityYear="1823" box="[308,429,1330,1356]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Anacharis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB748067A39FAE2FE0E4A54" box="[308,429,1330,1356]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">Anacharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from Chinese Turkestan with the same denomination (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA385B4FFB748067FC3FAE2FAC94A54" author="Kieffer J. J." box="[1230,1386,1330,1356]" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" pagination="329 - 342" refId="ref20310" refString="Kieffer J. J. 1910. New exotic cynipids. Bollettino del Laboratorio di Entomoligia del Reale Istituto Superiore Agrario di Bologna 4: 329 - 342. [In French.]" type="journal article" year="1910">Kieffer 1910</bibRefCitation>
). The author changed the homonymy one year later as part of a revision and correction on the names of different species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFB748067AA5FAA8FD8C4A8A" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[424,559,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Cynipoidea">Cynipoidea</taxonomicName>
and Evanoidea (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA385B4FFB7480679FBFAA8FC314A8B" author="Kieffer J. J." box="[758,914,1400,1427]" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" pagination="121" refId="ref20344" refString="Kieffer J. J. 1911. Changes in the names of evaniids and cynipids. Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana 41 (1909): 121. [In French.]" type="journal article" year="1911">Kieffer 1911</bibRefCitation>
), thus resulting in one American species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFB748067BB3FA4CFE5C4AAE" authority="Kieffer, 1909" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1909" box="[190,511,1436,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Anacharis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB748067BB3FA4CFEF94AAE" box="[190,346,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">A. flavicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA385B4FFB748067A6CFA4CFE5C4AAE" author="Kieffer J. J." box="[353,511,1436,1462]" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" pagination="57 - 96" refId="ref20278" refString="Kieffer J. J. 1909. Description of new zoophagous cynipids. Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire naturelle de Metz 26: 57 - 96. [In French.]" type="journal article" year="1909">Kieffer, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and one Palaearctic species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFB748067857FA4CFB174AAE" authority="Kieffer, 1911" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" box="[858,1204,1436,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidicornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB748067857FA4CFBAD4AAE" box="[858,1038,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">A. flavidicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA385B4FFB748067F18FA4CFB174AAE" author="Kieffer J. J." box="[1045,1204,1436,1462]" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" pagination="121" refId="ref20344" refString="Kieffer J. J. 1911. Changes in the names of evaniids and cynipids. Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana 41 (1909): 121. [In French.]" type="journal article" year="1911">Kieffer, 1911</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DF845FFB748067BB0FA0DFAD44903" blockId="10.[189,1399,1501,1563]" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">
When studying the 
<typeStatus id="548946E7FFB748067AABFA0EFE7B4AE0" box="[422,472,1502,1528]" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFB748067909FA0DFCB04AEF" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" box="[516,787,1501,1527]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Anacharis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidicornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB748067909FA0DFCB04AEF" box="[516,787,1501,1527]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">Anacharis flavidicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it did not present the typical features of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFB748067BB0F9D0FE904902" authorityName="Dalman" authorityYear="1823" box="[189,307,1536,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Anacharis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB748067BB0F9D0FE904902" box="[189,307,1536,1562]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">Anacharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFB748067A68F9D0FE604902" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1835" box="[357,451,1536,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB748067A68F9D0FE604902" box="[357,451,1536,1562]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">Aegilips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
instead, being recombined into 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFB748067823F9D0FAD14903" authority="(Mata-Casanova et al. 2018)" baseAuthorityName="Mata-Casanova" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[814,1394,1536,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidicornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB748067823F9D0FB824902" box="[814,1057,1536,1562]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">Aegilips flavidicornis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA385B4FFB748067F3CF9D1FAC94903" author="Mata-Casanova N. &amp; Selfa J. &amp; Pujade-Villar J." box="[1073,1386,1536,1563]" pageId="10" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref20775" refString="Mata-Casanova N., Selfa J. &amp; Pujade-Villar J. 2018. Three new species of Anacharis Dalman, 1823 (Hymenoptera: Figitidae) with revised taxonomy and distribution records of Palaearctic and Indomalayan species. European Journal of Taxonomy 414: 1 - 25. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2018.414" type="journal article" year="2018">
Mata-Casanova 
<emphasis id="B9462457FFB748067FE1F9D1FA864902" box="[1260,1317,1536,1562]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="118">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
